efugee and prisoner affairs  By 2001  however  Cotting was settled in the United States  That was the year he became a U S  citizen and the year he earned his doctorate  It was also the year of the terrorist attacks on the World Trade Center and of his own decision to do something to help his adopted country in the aftermath  Cotting joined the U S  Army Medical Service Corps and  in 2004 as part of a Mental Health Advisory Team  traversed war torn Iraq assessing the psychological well being of U S  service members  Cotting traveled to 17 Forward Operations Bases in Iraq and Kuwait  which sometimes came under fire   One has to be a good follower before becoming a good leader  said Cotting   Here at VMI  you start at the bottom and you have a much better experience at interacting and leading individuals than you would get anywhere else  Lt  Col  Dave Cotting Associate Professor  Psychology Ph D  University of California Davis Specialty Leadership stress   coping  social personality psychology  and sports psychology     Share this entry Share on Facebook Share on Twitter Share on Google  Share on Linkedin Share on Tumblr Share on Reddit Share by Mail Stories   Videos Stories   Video Home Stories Slideshows Day in the Life Video Library Admissions Video More About Life at VMI Cadets Academics Athletics Challenge Alumni Faculty and Staff Apply Now Viewbook Links College Fairs FAQs Financial Aid Tuition   Fees Schedule VMI s Institutional Profile Follow  Then lead  Resources VMI CEEB Code  005858 Financial Aid FAFSA Code  003753 Students and their families are encouraged to use a variety of information sources to select a college and major  The State Council of Higher Education for Virginia  SCHEV  provides one such source that is available here  Contact Us VMI Office of Admissions 319 Letcher Avenue Lexington  VA 24450 P  540 464 7211 P  800 767 4207 F  540 464 7746 admissions vmi edu Don t do ordinary  EXPERIENCE VISIT APPLY COSTS   AID CONTACT Stories   Video You are 